  <programme start="20260305105700 +0100" stop="20260305112600 +0100" channel="Stingray Classica">
    <title lang="pl">Mozart - Divertimento No. 11, K. 251</title>
    <desc lang="pl">Lucerne Culture and Congress Center (KKL), Switzerland. The soloists from the Lucerne Festival Orchestra present Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's Divertimento No. 11 in D major, K. 251, known as the 'Nannerl-Septet'. Mozart composed it in 1776, probably on the occasion of his sister Maria Anna's name day, whose nickname was 'Nannerl'. The septet is scored for oboe, two horns, two violins, viola and double bass. This performance was recorded at Lucerne Culture and Congress Center (KKL), Switzerland, in 2020.</desc>
    <date>2020</date>
