  <programme start="20260307210400 +0100" stop="20260307213500 +0100" channel="Stingray Classica">
    <title lang="pl">Mahler - Songs on the Death of Children</title>
    <desc lang="pl">Sala Nezahualcóyotl, Mexico City. Mahler's Kindertotenlieder (Songs on the Death of Children) is a deeply personal song cycle for voice and orchestra inspired by Friedrich Rückert's poems about the loss of his children. The work's emotional depth comes from its unflinching portrayal of grief through a powerful juxtaposition of natural imagery and intimate parental pain. Audiences are captivated by the work's profound expression of universal human sorrow and the raw, restrained intensity of Mahler's masterful musical depiction of a parent's pain.</desc>
    <date>2012</date>
    <category lang="pl">concert</category>
