  <programme start="20260307213500 +0100" stop="20260307224900 +0100" channel="Stingray Classica">
    <title lang="pl">Symphony No. 5</title>
    <desc lang="pl">Sala Nezahualcóyotl, Mexico City, Mexico. Composed between 1901 and 1902, Mahler's Fifth Symphony marked a significant shift in his compositional style, moving away from vocal elements toward a purely symphonic structure. It's a work of immense scope and emotional depth, known for its rich orchestral textures and intricate counterpoint. The symphony is characterized by its innovative use of structure and its exploration of powerful themes, including a profound funeral march, a tender Adagietto for strings and harp, and a vibrant, triumphant finale.</desc>
    <date>2012</date>
    <category lang="pl">concert</category>
    <icon src="https://ptv-prod.wpcdn.pl/media/akpa4984469.jpg" />
