  <programme start="20260308044500 +0100" stop="20260308051800 +0100" channel="Stingray Classica">
    <title lang="pl">Bach - Partita for Violin No. 2 (BWV 1004)</title>
    <desc lang="pl">St. Thomas Church, Leipzig, Germany. Celebrated German violinist Isabelle Faust performs J. S. Bach's Partita No. 2 in D minor (BWV 1004). The work is part of the composer's well-known Sonatas and Partitas for Solo Violin (BWV 1001-1006). Partita No. 2 is made up of four dance movements, concluded by its famous Chaconne, a monumental piece within the violin repertoire. In this Chaconne, Bach develops a series of continuous variations from a theme, exploring a complex range of harmonic possibilities. This performance was recorded at St. Thomas Church in Leipzig, Germany, in 2020.</desc>
    <date>2020</date>
