    <title lang="pl">Chamber music by Haydn, Chausson &amp; Mendelssohn</title>
    <desc lang="pl">Auditorio Sony, Reina Sofía School of Music, Madrid, Spain. Discover the next generation of chamber music talent from the Reina Sofía School of Music. In the first half of this program, Trio Michelangeli presents two masterpieces: Joseph Haydn's Piano Trio No. 39 in G major, nicknamed 'Gypsy', followed by the romanticism of Ernest Chausson's Piano Trio in G minor. The concert concludes with a performance by the Erinys Quartet of Felix Mendelssohn's inventive String Quartet No. 2 in A minor. This performance was recorded at Auditorio Sony of the Reina Sofía School of Music in Madrid, Spain, on June 7, 2024.</desc>
